          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GEMUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detectors were thin sheets of the metals",
                "Ag, Rh and In of dimensions 6 by 10 cm. After",
                "irradiation the detectors were assayed with a",
                "Geiger-Muller tube."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A cylindrical block of paraffin, 15 cm in diameter",
                "and 17 cm high, contained a Ra-Be bulb located on the",
                "axis 6 cm from the top surface. The thin detectors",
                "were placed on top of the paraffin cylinder and the",
                "scatterer, usually blocks of metal the same size as",
                "the detector, were placed on top of the detector. In",
                "some cases a sheet of Cd metal, containing 0.218",
                "g/cm2, was interposed between the paraffin and the",
                "detector. This served as a filter to cut out neutrons",
                "of the C group. After irradiation for a given length",
                "of time the detectors were placed around a",
                "Geiger-Muller tube counter and the activity obtained",
                "with the help of a thyratron \"scale of two\" recording",
                "system. An activity measurement was used to derive",
                "the scattering cross sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Percentage of scattered neutrons was measured (n/n0).",
                "This quantity is related to a combination of single",
                "scattering (sigmas) and capture cross (sigmac)",
                "sections as n/n0 = (N*a*sigmas/(2*N*b*(sigmas+sigmac))",
                "*[1-exp(-2*N*b*(sigmas +sigmac)*x)], where N is the",
                "number of atoms/cm2 of the scatterer, and a and b",
                "quantities which come in because of the solid angles",
                "involved. The quantity N*(sigmas+sigmac) is the usual",
                "absorption coefficient, and the factor 2 arises since",
                "the neutrons traverse the scatterer twice. The",
                "calculation does show, however, that the slope of the",
                "curve for small thicknesses is proportional to",
                "N*sigmas, and the saturation value is governed by",
                "sigmas/(sigmas+sigmac). Thus the relative scattering",
                "cross section can be obtained and some idea as to the",
                "ratio of scattering cross section to total cross",
                "section."
              ]
            }
          ],
